Description: Async network management tool with D-Bus daemon
 netctl is an async network management tool built on tokio for high
 performance. It provides comprehensive network administration capabilities
 including:
 .
  * netctld daemon with CR D-Bus interface (org.crrouter.NetworkControl)
  * nccli command-line tool with --use-dbus support
  * Interface management (up/down, IP configuration)
  * WiFi support (scan, connect, regulatory domain)
  * Access point mode with hostapd integration
  * DHCP server configuration with dora
  * DNS management with unbound integration
  * Routing control
  * Bridge and VLAN support
  * VPN support (OpenVPN, WireGuard, IPsec, Tor via Arti)
  * NetworkManager D-Bus compatibility layer
  * Plugin system for extensibility
 .
 The package includes both netctld (modern CR D-Bus daemon) and netctl
 (NetworkManager compatibility daemon). Use netctld for new installations.
